ISSN: 1369-8478. \n\n- Bruschetta, M., Maran, F., Beghi, A., and Minen, D., Sept. 4, 2014. An MPC based Motion Cueing Algorithm with side slip dynamics. In: A. Kemeny, F. Colombet, F. Merienne, and S. Espi\u00b4e eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2014 Europe_ . \n\n- Bruschetta, M., Maran, F., Cenedese, C., Beghi, A., and Minen, D., Sept. 7, 2016. An MPC-Based Motion Cueing implementation with Time-Varying Prediction and drivers skills characterization. In: A. Kemeny, F. Merienne, F. Colombet, and S. Espi\u00b4e eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2016 Europe_ . Driving Simulation Association. Paris, France, pp. 11\u2013 20. \n\n- Bruschetta, M., Mendola, D. L., Beghi, A., and Minen, D., Sept. 5, 2018. An MPC based Motion Cueing Algorithm with side slip dynamics. In: A. Kemeny, F. Colombet, F. Merienne, and S. Espi\u00b4e eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2018 Europe VR_ . Driving Simulation Association. Antibes, France, pp. 55\u201359. \n\n- Chadha, A., Jain, V., Lazcano, A., and Shyrokau, B., 2023. Computationally-efficient Motion Cueing Algorithm via Model Predictive Control. English. In: _Proceedings - 2023 IEEE International Conference on Mechatronics, ICM 2023_ . United States: IEEE. \n\n**Stuttgart, 24-26 Sep 2025** \n\n**-6-** \n\n**DSC 2025 Europe**<sup>VR</sup> \n\n**Craig Brown** **_et al._** \n\n- _DMG-1_ 2025. `https://www.dynisma.com/dmg- 1` . Accessed: 2025-04-14. \n\n- Fang, Z. and Kemeny, A., 2012. Motion Cueing Algorithms for a Real-Time Automobile Driving Simulator. In: A. Kemeny ed. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2012 Europe_ . \n\n- Fang, Z. and Kemeny, A., 2014. Review and Prospects of Renault\u2019s MPC Based Motion Cueing Algorithm for Driving Simulator. In: A. Kemeny, F. Merienne, and S. Espi\u00b4e eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2014 Europe VR_ . Paris, France. \n\n- Fang, Z., Wautier, D., and Kemeny, A., Sept. 4, 2019. Development and applications of a fast MPC based motion cueing algorithm. In: A. Kemeny, F. Colombet, F. Merienne, and S. Espi\u00b4e eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2019 Europe VR_ . Driving Simulation Association. Strasbourg, France, pp. 109\u2013116. \n\n- Sept. 14, 2021. Renault\u2019s new MPC based motion cueing algorithm development. In: A. Kemeny, J.-R. Chardonnet, and F. Colombet eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2021 Europe VR_ . Driving Simulation Association. Munich, Germany, pp. 149\u2013158. \n\n- Garrett, N. and Best, M., 2013. Model predictive driving simulator motion cueing algorithm with actuator-based constraints. _Vehicle System Dynamics_ , 51(8), pp. 1151\u20131172. `https://doi. org/10.1080/00423114.2013.783219` . \n\n- Ghafarian, M., Watson, M., Mohajer, N., Nahavandi, D., Kebria, P. M., and Mohamed, S., 2023. A Review of Dynamic Vehicular Motion Simulators: Systems and Algorithms. _IEEE Access_ , 11, pp. 36331\u201336348. \n\n- Grottoli, M., Cleij, D., Pretto, P., Lemmens, Y., Happee, R., and B\u00a8ulthoff, H., Dec. 2018. Objective evaluation of prediction strategies for optimization-based motion cueing. _SIMULATION_ , 95, p. 003754971881597. `https : / / doi . org / 10 . 1177 / 0037549718815972` . \n\n- Hu, J. and Zhang, H., 2014. Globally asymptotically stable saturated PID controllers for a double integrator with constant disturbance. _International Journal of Robust and Nonlinear Control_ , 24(10), pp. 1488\u20131504. \n\n   - based Motion Cueing Algorithm Using Washout Speed and Grey Wolf Optimizer. In: IEEE Press. \n\n   - Qazani, M. R. C., Asadi, H., Najdovski, Z., Alsanwy, S., Zakarya, M., Alam, F., Ouakad, H. M., Lim, C. P., and Nahavandi, S., 2024. High-fidelity learning-based motion cueing algorithm by bypassing worst-case scenario-based tuning technique. _Cognitive Robotics_ , 4, pp. 116\u2013127. ISSN: 2667-2413. \n\n   - Rao, V. and Bernstein, D., 2001. Naive control of the double integrator. _IEEE Control Systems Magazine_ , 21(5), pp. 86\u201397. \n\n   - Scalera, L., Giusti, A., Cosmo, V., Riedl, M., Vidoni, R., and Matt, D., June 2020. Application of Dynamically Scaled Safety Zones Based on the ISO/TS 15066:2016 for Collaborative Robotics. _International Journal of Mechanics and Control_ , 21, pp. 41\u201350. \n\n   - Schneider, P. and Xhafa, F., 2022. Chapter 3 - Anomaly detection: Concepts and methods. In: P. Schneider and F. Xhafa eds. _Anomaly Detection and Complex Event Processing over IoT Data Streams_ . Academic Press, pp. 49\u201366. \n\n   - Song, C. and Lau, D., Aug. 2022. Workspace-Based Model Predictive Control for Cable-Driven Robots. _IEEE Transactions on Robotics_ , 38, pp. 2577\u20132596. \n\n   - Telban, R. and Cardullo, F., 2005. _Motion Cueing Algorithm Development: Human-Centered Linear and Nonlinear Approaches_ . Tech. rep. CR-2005-213747. NASA. \n\n   - Tyan, F. and Bernstein, D. S., 1999. Global stabilization of systems containing a double integrator using a saturated linear controller. _International Journal of Robust and Nonlinear Control_ , 9(15), pp. 1143\u20131156. \n\n   - van der Ploeg, J., Cleij, D., Pool, D., Mulder, M., and B\u00a8ulthoff, H., 2020. Sensitivity Analysis of an MPC-based Motion Cueing Algorithm for a Curve Driving Scenario. In: A. Kemeny, J.-R. Chardonnet, and F. Colombet eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2020 Europe_ . Antibes, France. \n\n   - Zhang, J. and Sanderson, A. C., 2009. JADE: Adaptive Differential Evolution With Optional External Archive. _IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation_ , 13(5), pp. 945\u2013958. \n\n- Jain, V., Lazcano, A., Happee, R., and Shyrokau, B., 2023. _Motion Cueing Algorithm for Effective Motion Perception: A frequencysplitting MPC Approach_ . arXiv: `2309.01689 [cs.RO]` . Available at: \u00a1 `https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.01689` \u00bf. \n\n- Katliar, M., Winkel, K. de, Venrooij, J., Pretto, P., and B\u00a8ulthoff, H., Sept. 2015. Impact of MPC Prediction Horizon on Motion Cueing Fidelity. In: H. B\u00a8ulthoff, A. Kemeny, and P. Pretto eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2015 Europe_ . T\u00a8ubingen, Germany. \n\n- Khusro, Y. R., Zheng, Y., Grottoli, M., and Shyrokau, B., 2020. MPC-Based Motion-Cueing Algorithm for a 6-DOF Driving Simulator with Actuator Constraints. _Vehicles_ , 2(4), pp. 625\u2013647. \n\n- Kolff, M., Venrooij, J., Schwienbacher, M., Pool, D., and Mulder, M., Oct. 2022. Motion Cueing Quality Comparison of Driving Simulators using Oracle Motion Cueing. In: A. Kemeny, J.-R. Chardonnet, F. Colombet, F. Merienne, and S. Espi\u00b4e eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2022 Europe VR_ . Strasbourg, France. \n\n- Lamprecht, A., Steffen, D., Haecker, J., and Graichen, K., Sept. 4, 2019. Comparison between a Filter and an MPC based MCA in an Offline Simulator Study. In: A. Kemeny, F. Colombet, F. Merienne, and S. Espi\u00b4e eds. _Proceedings of the Driving Simulation Conference 2019 Europe VR_ . Driving Simulation Association. Strasbourg, France, pp. 101\u2013107. \n\n- Munir, S., Hovd, M., Fang, Z., Olaru, S., and Kemeny, A., 2017. Complexity reduction in motion cueing algorithm for the ULTIMATE driving simulator. _IFAC-PapersOnLine_ , 50(1). 20th IFAC World Congress, pp. 10729\u201310734. \n\n- Papamichail, C., Stark, D., and Gambi, A., 2025. Scenario-Based Testing with BeamNG.tech (Hands-On Training). In: _2025 IEEE Conference on Software Testing, Verification and Validation (ICST)_ , pp. 767\u2013768. \n\n- Pham, D.-A., Pham, T. N., and Nguyen, D.-T., 2023. Novel model predictive control-based motion cueing algorithm for compensating centrifugal acceleration in KUKA robocoaster-based driving simulators. _Science Progress_ , 106(4), p. 00368504231204759. \n\n- Qazani, M. R. C., Asadi, H., Mohamed, S., Alqumsan, A. A., Rahimzadeh, G., Lim, C. P., and Nahavandi, S., 2021. An MPC- \n\n**Stuttgart, 24-26 Sep 2025** \n\n**-7-** \n",
        "gemini_summary": "This reference list serves as the supporting academic framework for the paper **\"Meeting Workspace Constraints\"** by Craig Brown et al. The citations contextualize the research within the evolution of **Motion Cueing Algorithms (MCA)**, specifically highlighting the tension between two dominant paradigms:\n\n*   **Model Predictive Control (MPC):** The bibliography features extensive documentation on MPC-based cueing, including foundational works by **Bruschetta et al.**, **Fang and Kemeny**, and **Khusro et al.** These works established the high fidelity and constraint-handling capabilities of MPC, as well as the industry\u2019s ongoing struggle to manage its computational and tuning complexity.\n*   **Classical Washout Filters (CWF):** The inclusion of texts like **Telban and Cardullo (2005)** and various papers by **Brown (2023, 2024)** highlights the industry-standard \"classical\" approach. The list emphasizes the focus on simplicity, ease of implementation, and the preference for consistent cueing \"character\" in industrial settings.\n*   **Hybrid and Optimization Methods:** The references point toward modern efforts to bridge the gap between these two worlds. This includes research on **Piecewise Affine (PWA) functions** and **Look-up Tables (LUTs)** for efficiency (e.g., **Chadha et al.**, **Munir et al.**), as well as novel control strategies using PID or derivative-free optimization (**Brown et al., 2016**; **Zhang and Sanderson, 2009**) to stabilize systems when physical workspace limits are reached.\n\n**Overall Significance:**\nThe bibliography demonstrates that the authors are not working in a vacuum; rather, they are addressing a known \"industrial-academic gap.\" By grounding their hybrid \"MPC-as-a-filter\" approach in both classic control theory (e.g., **Hu and Zhang**, **Rao and Bernstein**) and contemporary simulation research (**BeamNG**, **ProCue**), the authors provide a rigorous technical foundation for a simplified, universal workflow for diverse, multi-simulator facilities."
    }
}